103.2	Activism	Activism	Activism consists of intentional efforts to promote, impede or direct social, political, economic, or environmental change. Activism can take a wide range of forms from writing letters to newspapers or politicians, political campaigning, economic activism such as boycotts or preferentially patronizing businesses, rallies, street marches, strikes, sit-ins, and hunger strikes.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/c/c3/1963_march_on_washington.jpg/220px-1963_march_on_washington.jpg
